The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves using denoising autoencoders for score estimation and iterative inference, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of corrupted feedforward predictors, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of their approach over conditional random fields, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL).
